race.comment: MOONWALK (8) showed ability in her first campaign then returned with an emphatic win fresh at Northam. Straight to 1400 and Pike stays aboard. Looks the one to follow up. SAAM TIME LUCKY (3) has been racing well and last time ran on hard to just miss over this journey. More seasoned than most and will be tough to hold out late. HOLLER NUFF (4) was close to the winner fresh then got off the mark last time when relished the extra ground. Progressive and can measure up again. SPLIT THE GEE (2) has been mixing form and but has strong 1200m figures in tougher races. First try this trip and worth including. RUBENS' CEILING (5) pinged the gates on debut at Northam and led throughout for an effortless win. Stiffer test here and drawn out but has good upside.
